  "text": "It is also possible that the TCP/IP congestion control algorithms can delay a single transmission that arrives at an inappropriate time. In the face of fluctuating network traffic, these algorithms can behave chaotically and unnecessarily throttle single transmissions [CITATION_1] . This happens not as a result of an overall increase in traffic through the network, but instead as an anomaly in the algorithm. These anomalies quickly are resolved, and subsequent sends will be unaffected until the algorithm becomes unstable again.",
